title: Body Building
details: Bodybuilding is the use of progressive resistance exercise to control and develop one's muscles by muscle hypertrophy for aesthetic purposes. It is distinct from similar activities such as powerlifting because it focuses on physical appearance instead of strength.

title: Gymnastic Rings
details: The rings, also known as steady rings or still rings (in contrast to flying rings), is an artistic gymnastics apparatus and the event that uses it.

title: Core
details: The most effective core exercises are dead bug, side plank, front plant, vertical leg crunches, flutter kicks, Russian twists and the hollow body hold and hang. The core is a collection of muscles that stabilize, rotate and move the spine. A healthy core translates into a stronger lower back and better balance.
